281
00:16:03,210 --> 00:16:06,084
He, um, he did odd jobs, at Della's.

282
00:16:06,084 --> 00:16:08,750
Oh, he did other things, too.

283
00:16:09,111 --> 00:16:11,704
Tell them what you saw.

284
00:16:28,169 --> 00:16:30,487
Della was messing with Frank?

285
00:16:30,601 --> 00:16:32,651
It's, it's just what I saw.

286
00:16:32,651 --> 00:16:34,729
You never told anyone?

287
00:16:35,462 --> 00:16:39,346
People shouldn't get messed up
in other people's relationships.

288
00:16:53,038 --> 00:16:54,544
I don't know.

289
00:16:55,091 --> 00:16:56,970
No.

290
00:16:57,210 --> 00:16:58,335
Never seen him.

291
00:16:58,335 --> 00:16:59,377
J.T. simms.

292
00:16:59,377 --> 00:17:02,044
Hung on the corner here for two 
years, right in front of your stoop.

293
00:17:02,044 --> 00:17:03,636
Nope.

294
00:17:06,070 --> 00:17:08,118
Thanks a million.

295
00:17:12,931 --> 00:17:15,943
- She give you anything?
- Told me to go pound sand.

296
00:17:15,943 --> 00:17:18,468
Who else can we find to lie to us?

297
00:17:19,560 --> 00:17:21,217
You still seeing that girl?

298
00:17:21,217 --> 00:17:23,825
Elisa? Nah.

299
00:17:23,825 --> 00:17:25,943
What happened?

300
00:17:25,943 --> 00:17:29,004
Nothing. Just, uh, time to move on.

301
00:17:29,534 --> 00:17:32,428
So you're back in the hunt?

302
00:17:32,720 --> 00:17:35,482
Uh... I guess.

303
00:17:35,482 --> 00:17:39,576
Well, a couple of nurses at 
st. Joe's, up for a night out.

304
00:17:39,701 --> 00:17:41,594
Your wife coming?

305
00:17:44,823 --> 00:17:47,358
Someone's trying 
to get our attention.

306
00:17:54,601 --> 00:17:56,586
You looking for stick Simms?

307
00:17:58,152 --> 00:17:59,436
I'm putting this place on the market,

308
00:17:59,436 --> 00:18:02,238
hoping someone's 
looking for a tax write-off.

309
00:18:02,560 --> 00:18:05,078
Ever think about opening it again?

310
00:18:05,078 --> 00:18:06,838
Not in this neighborhood.

311
00:18:06,838 --> 00:18:10,366
We're aware of whoever killed my parents
probably lives within two blocks of here.

312
00:18:10,366 --> 00:18:13,191
I can't smile and 
serve them every day.

313
00:18:14,316 --> 00:18:15,938
So, um...

314
00:18:15,938 --> 00:18:17,775
you wanted to know about Frank?

315
00:18:17,775 --> 00:18:20,778
Well, Tyra said he might have
been close with your parents.

316
00:18:20,778 --> 00:18:22,103
With my mom maybe.

317
00:18:22,103 --> 00:18:25,966
Why's that? / She had a weakness 
for men who needed to be saved.

318
00:18:25,966 --> 00:18:28,035
Um, are you hiring?

319
00:18:28,035 --> 00:18:30,205
No, honey. I'm sorry.

320
00:18:32,196 --> 00:18:34,459
Do you know Frank's last name?

321
00:18:34,459 --> 00:18:35,767
Morgan, I think.

322
00:18:35,767 --> 00:18:37,425
Buster morgan, the boxer?

323
00:18:37,425 --> 00:18:39,825
Yeah. My dad called him that.

324
00:18:39,825 --> 00:18:41,143
You know where he stays?

325
00:18:41,143 --> 00:18:43,139
He never had a permanent situation.

326
00:18:43,139 --> 00:18:44,687
Why are you asking about Frank?

327
00:18:44,687 --> 00:18:46,699
His name came up is all.

328
00:18:48,494 --> 00:18:51,835
Guy from the shelter said try 
the tent city round the corner.

329
00:18:51,835 --> 00:18:54,256
It's behind big Ed's gym.

330
00:18:54,385 --> 00:18:56,065
You know this area 
pretty good, huh?

331
00:18:56,065 --> 00:18:57,565
I grew up two blocks over.

332
00:18:57,565 --> 00:19:00,862
I used to go to that gym
and watch the guys spar.

333
00:19:01,503 --> 00:19:03,009
You ever get in the ring?

334
00:19:03,009 --> 00:19:05,211
No, I got hit enough 
in my own house.

335
00:19:05,342 --> 00:19:07,505
Frank, Frank morgan?

336
00:19:13,328 --> 00:19:14,515
I'm Frank.

337
00:19:14,515 --> 00:19:17,453
- What? 
- It's Will jeffries, buster.

338
00:19:17,552 --> 00:19:19,139
Will who?

339
00:19:20,508 --> 00:19:22,732
We're here about Della lincoln.

340
00:19:22,732 --> 00:19:25,372
- You know Della?
- We're investigating her murder.

341
00:19:26,602 --> 00:19:28,837
Right. Stupid.

342
00:19:29,018 --> 00:19:30,298
Della's gone.

343
00:19:30,298 --> 00:19:34,184
We got a witness saw you and 
Della kissing the night she died.

344
00:19:34,184 --> 00:19:35,686
- Tom?
- Tom's dead, too.

345
00:19:35,686 --> 00:19:37,321
Because it was a mistake.

346
00:19:37,321 --> 00:19:39,153
What was?

347
00:19:41,507 --> 00:19:43,748
Come on, Frank.

348
00:19:44,036 --> 00:19:47,191
Tell us what happened that night.

349
00:19:51,780 --> 00:19:53,713
Did you lose something?

350
00:19:55,962 --> 00:19:57,547
Where'd you get that?

351
00:19:57,547 --> 00:20:00,469
Tom found them in the trash.

352
00:20:01,164 --> 00:20:02,977
You gotta take them, Frank.

353
00:20:02,977 --> 00:20:04,812
You can't forget, 
not even for a day.

354
00:20:04,812 --> 00:20:06,303
They make me tired.

355
00:20:06,303 --> 00:20:08,614
They keep you right. / I know.

356
00:20:08,614 --> 00:20:11,443
We're gonna get 
you back on your feet.

357
00:20:11,558 --> 00:20:14,114
No. No. No, Frank.

358
00:20:14,114 --> 00:20:16,255
What is going on?

359
00:20:19,197 --> 00:20:20,678
I'm, I'm...

360
00:20:20,678 --> 00:20:22,195
I'll just...
I won't come back.

361
00:20:22,195 --> 00:20:25,444
I'm sorry. / Frank. Frank!

362
00:20:25,696 --> 00:20:27,879
Della cares about you,
just like I do,

363
00:20:27,879 --> 00:20:30,979
but there's different kinds of caring.
You can't confuse the two.

364
00:20:30,979 --> 00:20:33,899
I know. You can't go kissing
on other men's wives.

365
00:20:33,899 --> 00:20:37,321
Oh, I won't. I won't.

366
00:20:37,321 --> 00:20:40,254
Give me that stuff.

367
00:20:43,568 --> 00:20:46,299
Dinner crowd's gonna be in soon.

368
00:20:48,106 --> 00:20:49,865
He didn't kick me out,

369
00:20:49,865 --> 00:20:51,601
when by rights, he could've.

370
00:20:51,601 --> 00:20:53,334
What were E meds for?

371
00:20:53,617 --> 00:20:55,519
I get extreme.

372
00:20:55,519 --> 00:20:57,445
Did you get extreme that night?

373
00:20:57,445 --> 00:20:58,869
Hurt Della and Tom?

374
00:20:58,869 --> 00:21:02,546
Hurt them? They was the 
only thing holding me together.

375
00:21:03,780 --> 00:21:07,336
Frank, do you remember
a fight between Della and Tyra?

376
00:21:09,360 --> 00:21:12,382
Della caught her putting on makeup.

377
00:21:12,823 --> 00:21:13,958
What do you mean?

378
00:21:13,958 --> 00:21:16,308
Her boyfriend hit her

379
00:21:16,308 --> 00:21:20,559
and Tyra was trying to 
cover up the bruise.

380
00:21:21,758 --> 00:21:25,335
You couldn't fool Della, see?

381
00:21:34,907 --> 00:21:36,702
J.T. simms?

382
00:21:39,407 --> 00:21:41,484
What'd I do?

383
00:21:42,217 --> 00:21:43,937
You tell us.

384
00:21:43,937 --> 00:21:47,743
It's about the murders at the 
chicken and ribs place, last year.

385
00:21:48,078 --> 00:21:49,365
Don't remember nothing about it.

386
00:21:49,365 --> 00:21:50,988
You sure?

387
00:21:51,575 --> 00:21:56,091
Because if my boys saw me almost 
get bitch-slapped by an old woman,

388
00:21:56,091 --> 00:21:58,220
I know I'd remember.

389
00:21:58,334 --> 00:22:01,036
You better get biggie here
out of my face.

390
00:22:01,036 --> 00:22:02,599
Della made you look small.

391
00:22:02,599 --> 00:22:04,836
Maybe you went back later
to settle the score.

392
00:22:04,836 --> 00:22:09,109
Using that gun you flashed at Derek
jackson and Joe moore that night.

393
00:22:10,730 --> 00:22:12,206
I ain't talking no more.

394
00:22:12,206 --> 00:22:13,699
Why not?

395
00:22:13,699 --> 00:22:15,068
Who you scared of, Joe?

396
00:22:15,068 --> 00:22:17,567
Who you think runs the game now?

397
00:22:17,733 --> 00:22:19,970
So he took your place out there, huh?

398
00:22:19,970 --> 00:22:21,589
How'd that happen?

399
00:22:21,854 --> 00:22:25,052
Hey, stick, we got you 
at the scene that night.

400
00:22:25,052 --> 00:22:27,847
You beefed with two of the victims,
got priors with the same M.O.

401
00:22:27,847 --> 00:22:31,433
And don't play that cripple card.
Triple murderers get no love.

402
00:22:37,000 --> 00:22:40,335
I've seen Joe outside
the restaurant the next day.

403
00:22:46,899 --> 00:22:51,103
