to the detective on this job.

406
00:23:03,019 --> 00:23:04,682
That ain't you?

407
00:23:05,650 --> 00:23:06,854
Not anymore.

408
00:23:06,854 --> 00:23:08,728
Ask for detective Vera.

409
00:23:09,763 --> 00:23:11,498
Friend in there?

410
00:23:11,848 --> 00:23:14,125
Yeah.

411
00:23:14,309 --> 00:23:15,911
I'm sorry.

412
00:23:19,092 --> 00:23:21,847
Check out homicide barbie.

413
00:23:24,487 --> 00:23:26,833
Your boy Derek in there?

414
00:23:26,833 --> 00:23:28,872
- Yep. 
- Roll with me,

415
00:23:28,872 --> 00:23:30,483
be my soldier.

416
00:23:30,483 --> 00:23:33,855
You don't got to worry about 
something like that happening to you.

417
00:23:34,170 --> 00:23:35,695
- Yo, dawg...
- yo, I ain't your dawg!

418
00:23:35,695 --> 00:23:37,236
Then what are you?

419
00:23:37,236 --> 00:23:40,227
Somebody you got to step around.

420
00:23:40,227 --> 00:23:41,788
Take a look.

421
00:23:41,788 --> 00:23:43,964
See what I can do?

422
00:23:46,326 --> 00:23:49,745
You saying you took 
your own boy out?

423
00:23:50,964 --> 00:23:53,549
Maybe you can be my soldier.

424
00:24:00,801 --> 00:24:02,533
It was biblical, man.

425
00:24:02,533 --> 00:24:03,515
Ice cold.

426
00:24:03,515 --> 00:24:06,081
And you just believe him,
just rolled over, give up your turf?

427
00:24:06,081 --> 00:24:08,140
That brother turned hard, man.

428
00:24:08,140 --> 00:24:09,556
He backed it up,

429
00:24:09,556 --> 00:24:11,058
came down on my crew.

430
00:24:11,058 --> 00:24:13,301
Where do we find Joe?

431
00:24:13,879 --> 00:24:15,754
Man I tell you that, I get killed.

432
00:24:15,754 --> 00:24:18,333
Not if he goes away for this.

433
00:24:18,333 --> 00:24:22,146
Triple murder gets you a date
with the needle real quick.

434
00:24:25,734 --> 00:24:28,717
So we're off Frank as a suspect?

435
00:24:28,717 --> 00:24:31,876
He's goofed in the head,
but he doesn't have murder in him.

436
00:24:31,876 --> 00:24:33,972
Told us Tyra's secret, though.

437
00:24:33,972 --> 00:24:36,553
Her boyfriend Jammal 
was beating her up,

438
00:24:36,553 --> 00:24:38,626
and Della was wise to it.

439
00:24:38,626 --> 00:24:41,794
Scotty called in.
They're looking to pick up Joe moore.

440
00:24:41,794 --> 00:24:44,967
Derek's friend? / Yeah, guess he 
bragged to Simms about being the shooter.

441
00:24:44,967 --> 00:24:46,997
That kid? He was 
in shock at the scene.

442
00:24:46,997 --> 00:24:48,589
Playing dumb?

443
00:24:50,539 --> 00:24:52,997
Something hinky in this lab report.

444
00:24:52,997 --> 00:24:55,086
- Like what?
- Well, the first time they ran the prints,

445
00:24:55,086 --> 00:24:58,013
they excluded 
matches for the victims.

446
00:24:58,013 --> 00:25:00,115
They did a blanket search this time.

447
00:25:00,115 --> 00:25:05,099
And Derek's prints are
all over Della and Tom's shoes.

448
00:25:06,388 --> 00:25:08,236
Dragging the bodies?

449
00:25:08,236 --> 00:25:09,819
Oh, god.

450
00:25:09,819 --> 00:25:12,280
Tell me Derek wasn't in on this.

451
00:25:12,280 --> 00:25:15,138
Derek and Joe were pals, right, Lil?

452
00:25:15,746 --> 00:25:18,824
Maybe an inside job gone bad.

453
00:25:31,168 --> 00:25:33,258
We wake you, Joe?

454
00:25:37,044 --> 00:25:38,563
Yeah, can I get 
a coke or something?

455
00:25:38,563 --> 00:25:40,246
Why don't we visit here a minute.

456
00:25:40,246 --> 00:25:42,347
You had a busy year.

457
00:25:42,347 --> 00:25:44,645
Possession, ag-assault,

458
00:25:44,645 --> 00:25:46,524
assault with intent.

459
00:25:46,524 --> 00:25:49,006
Taking down Della's gave
you a taste, is that it?

460
00:25:49,006 --> 00:25:52,519
How'd it work that night? Did Derek 
leave the back door open for you or what?

461
00:25:52,771 --> 00:25:55,120
- Why you talking about Derek?
- You and him robbed that place.

462
00:25:55,120 --> 00:25:57,223
Maybe so you could pay for that 
sweet escalade you're pushing.

463
00:25:57,223 --> 00:26:00,483
Have some respect, all right?
You know, Derek is dead.

464
00:26:01,461 --> 00:26:06,007
Well, he wasn't dead when he dragged
Della and Tom's body into the bathroom.

465
00:26:06,372 --> 00:26:08,251
We got those prints, Joe.

466
00:26:08,251 --> 00:26:11,891
Maybe Derek lost it after 
you shot Della and Tom.

467
00:26:11,891 --> 00:26:15,591
You couldn't trust him to shut up,
so you had to pop him, too.

468
00:26:15,591 --> 00:26:17,640
Nah, nah, me and Derek was tight.

469
00:26:17,640 --> 00:26:20,319
Yeah, but you were going 
different ways. Derek was straight.

470
00:26:20,319 --> 00:26:22,874
- He had no stomach for the life.
- Not like you.

471
00:26:22,874 --> 00:26:24,005
You were tough.

472
00:26:24,005 --> 00:26:28,520
Getting sick and tired of having no scratch
and getting hassled on the block, right?

473
00:26:28,520 --> 00:26:30,423
That night...

474
00:26:30,423 --> 00:26:32,966
was your coming out.

475
00:26:33,653 --> 00:26:36,879
You want to know where I was
at when Derek got shot?

476
00:26:37,628 --> 00:26:40,334
Taking a boot to the head
from my mom's boyfriend.

477
00:26:40,334 --> 00:26:41,698
Nine stitches.

478
00:26:41,698 --> 00:26:43,816
Ask at the Temple ER.

479
00:26:44,296 --> 00:26:48,476
So why'd you brag to everyone
you did the murders?

480
00:26:49,836 --> 00:26:53,254
You think anyone on that block's
looked at me since then?

481
00:26:58,057 --> 00:27:00,182
Tyra's here.

482
00:27:10,400 --> 00:27:12,443
Say, I got some kind of 
bench warrant or something?

483
00:27:12,443 --> 00:27:13,914
Yeah...

484
00:27:13,914 --> 00:27:16,677
This isn't really about the warrant.

485
00:27:17,499 --> 00:27:19,778
It's about Jammal.

486
00:27:29,255 --> 00:27:30,590
What about him?

487
00:27:30,590 --> 00:27:32,848
I know he hits you, Tyra.

488
00:27:32,848 --> 00:27:35,084
No, he don't.

489
00:27:42,865 --> 00:27:45,761
Della knew, too.

490
00:27:45,876 --> 00:27:48,435
And from what I hear about Della,
she could be pretty forceful

491
00:27:48,435 --> 00:27:50,406
if she wanted something.

492
00:27:50,406 --> 00:27:51,836
That's the truth.

493
00:27:51,836 --> 00:27:55,235
And I bet she wanted 
you to leave Jammal.

494
00:27:55,235 --> 00:27:58,135
That's what you were 
fighting about that day.

495
00:28:01,496 --> 00:28:04,525
We're talking about Della here.

496
00:28:04,525 --> 00:28:07,543
Don't you owe her the truth?

497
00:28:08,522 --> 00:28:11,305
She said I could come stay with her.

498
00:28:11,710 --> 00:28:13,767
Must have pissed 
Jammal off pretty good.

499
00:28:13,767 --> 00:28:16,597
Well, Jammal didn't know.

500
00:28:17,875 --> 00:28:21,122
If he was pissed at anyone...

501
00:28:21,257 --> 00:28:23,217
it was Derek.

502
00:28:23,217 --> 00:28:25,621
